{"lemma":"رَمْلُ","slug":"رَمْلُ","root":"ر.م.ل","root_slug":"ر-م-ل","root_link":"/words/roots/ر-م-ل","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":6,"pos_tags":["adj","noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":12},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n16696","n16700","n16701"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B1%D9%8E%D9%85%D9%92%D9%84%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"sand","tags":["uncountable"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"ellipsis of عِلْم الرَمْل (ʕilm ar-raml, “geomancy”)","tags":["abbreviation","alt-of","ellipsis"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of رَمَلَ (ramala) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb","obsolete"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"weak rain","tags":["obsolete"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a certain mode of music","tags":["obsolete"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of رَمَلَ (ramala) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb","obsolete"]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"sandy","tags":["obsolete"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to mix sand into","tags":["obsolete"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to plait together, to braid, or to cover with plaited ornaments","tags":["obsolete"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to go forward in a kind of trotting pace","tags":["obsolete"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to pour sand into","tags":["obsolete"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to defile, to smear, to adulterate etc.","tags":["obsolete"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"First attested as Old South Arabian 𐩧𐩣𐩡 (rml). An extension of the root ر م م (r m m)."},"ipa":["/raml/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n16696","headword_ar":"رَمَلَ","root":"rml","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"as syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ram~ala","text_ar":"رَمَّلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see the latter in two places.       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ramala AlHaSiyra","text_ar":"رَمَلَ الحَصِيرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [aor. app."},{"kind":"text","text":", and inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ramolN","text_ar":"رَمْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":";] and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Armlhu","text_ar":"ارملهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":";"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He wove"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nasaja","text_ar":"نَسَجَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", A 'Obeyd, T, or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saf~a","text_ar":"سَفَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", A 'Obeyd, S)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the mat"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of palm-leaves"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (T, S.) [Or]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ramala Als~ariyra","text_ar":"رَمَلَ السَّرِيرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and [so in the M, but in the K “ or ”]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHaSiyra","text_ar":"الحَصِيرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ramolN","text_ar":"رَمْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He ornamented the couch,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the mat, with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jawohar","text_ar":"جَوْهَر"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"jewels, precious stones, gems,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.], and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K.) [Or]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHaSiyra","text_ar":"الحَصِيرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Arml","text_ar":"ارمل","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ramalahu","text_ar":"رَمَلَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He made the weaving of the mat thin"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Har p. 55.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ramala Aln~asoja","text_ar":"رَمَلَ النَّسْجَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,) aor. and inf. n. as above; (TA;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Armlhu","text_ar":"ارملهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rm~lhu","text_ar":"رمّلهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M, K; the last omitted in the TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He made the woven thing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the weaving, thin."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ramala Als~ariyra","text_ar":"رَمَلَ السَّرِيرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) [aor. and] inf. n. as above; (TA;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Armlhu","text_ar":"ارملهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":";"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He wove"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ramala","text_ar":"رَمَلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ariyT","text_ar":"شَرِيط"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"palm leaves split and then plaited together"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (S, O, K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"some other thing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and made the same a back"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaEalahu ZahorFA","text_ar":"جَعَلَهُ ظَهْرًا"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to the couch."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K. [What is here called the “ back ” of the couch is app. so called as being likened to the back of a beast on which one rides: see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rumaAlN","text_ar":"رُمَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) Accord. to IKt,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ramalotu Alsyr","text_ar":"رَمَلْتُ السير"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. a mistranscription for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~ariyra","text_ar":"السَّرِيرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"] and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aromalotuhu","text_ar":"اَرْمَلْتُهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signify"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I wove the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"syr","text_ar":"سير"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sryr","text_ar":"سرير"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ariyT","text_ar":"شَرِيط"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of leaves,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fibres, of the palm-tree."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b2-  [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ramalotu Alqawola","text_ar":"رَمَلْتُ القَوْلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlwaSofa","text_ar":"الوَصْفَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I wove,"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"composed, the saying"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the description"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Phrases cited in the TA from two modern poets.)       -A3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ramala","text_ar":"رَمَلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, S, M, Mgh, Msb, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, Mgh, Msb,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ramalaAnN","text_ar":"رَمَلَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, M, Mgh, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ramalN","text_ar":"رَمَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, &c.) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maromalN","text_ar":"مَرْمَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) said of a man,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"harowala","text_ar":"هَرْوَلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He went a kind of trotting pace, between a walk and a run"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (S, Mgh, Msb, K; [in the M said to be “ less than"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alma$oYu","text_ar":"المَشْىُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and above"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEadowu","text_ar":"العَدْوُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; ” app., as is remarked in the TT, through inadvertence of a writer;]) i. e. (TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he was quick in his manner of walking,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and shook his shoulder-joints,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"leaping,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(so in the T accord. to the TT,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not leaping,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(so in the TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in doing so;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, TA;) while performing the circuitings round the Kaabeh, (T, Mgh, TA,) but only in some of those circuitings, exclusively of others, (TA,) which one does in imitation of the Prophet and his Companions, who did thus in order that the people of Mekkeh might know that there was in them strength; (T, TA;) and in going between Es-Safà and El-Marweh. (S, TA.) [It is also said of a camel: see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rataka","text_ar":"رَتَكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]       -A4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ramalN","text_ar":"رَمَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as an inf. n. [app. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ramila AlEaAmu","text_ar":"رَمِلَ العَامُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ramilati Als~anapu","text_ar":"رَمِلَتِ السَّنَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"] signifies The year's"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having little rain."},{"kind":"text","text":"(KL.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ramilato mino zawojihaA","text_ar":"رَمِلَتْ مِنْ زَوْجِهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":": see 4."}],"source_refs":["M","K","S","O","T","Mgh","Msb","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n16700","headword_ar":"رَمْلٌ","root":"rml","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Sand;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a kind of dust"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"earth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"well known:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, T, M, Msb, K:) ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ramolapN","text_ar":"رَمْلَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is its n. un.; (M, K;) a more special term than the former; (S;) signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a piece,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"portion,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tract,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"collection,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thereof:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, T, TA:) [and the former word is also sometimes used as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a tract,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"collection, of sand:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] the pl. [of mult.] is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ramaAlN","text_ar":"رَمَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, T, S, M, Msb, K) and [of pauc.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aromulN","text_ar":"اَرْمُلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M, K;) [and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aramilu","text_ar":"اَرَمِلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is used as a pl. pl., i. e. pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aromulN","text_ar":"اَرْمُلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; occurring in a verse cited in the TA, art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hj","text_ar":"هج"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b2-  [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^um~u rimaAlK","text_ar":"اُمُّ رِمَالٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"a name of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The hyena."},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISk, S.) ―         -b3-  [Hence also,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~amolu","text_ar":"الرَّمْلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA in this art., [in the Lexicons of Golius and Freytag, erroneously,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ramalN","text_ar":"رَمَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",]) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eilomu Alr~amoli","text_ar":"عِلْمُ الرَّمْلِ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eilomu AlxaT~i","text_ar":"عِلْمُ الخَطِّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (IAar, TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xT","text_ar":"خط"},{"kind":"text","text":",) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Geomancy,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain well-known science."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA in the present art. [See a description of it voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaT~a","text_ar":"خَطَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":".])"}],"source_refs":["M","Lth","T","Msb","K","TA","S"]},{"entry_id":"n16701","headword_ar":"رَمَلٌ","root":"rml","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Weak rain:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, T:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"little rain:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Har p. 55:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a small quantity"},{"kind":"text","text":"of rain: (ElUmawee, T, S, M, K:) one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSaAbahumo ramalN mino","text_ar":"اَصَابَهُمْ رَمَلٌ مِنْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maTarK","text_ar":"مَطَرٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A small quantity of rain fell upon them:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(El-Umawee, T, M:) but Sh says, “ I have not heard"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ramalN","text_ar":"رَمَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in this sense except on the authority of El-Umawee: ” (TA:) the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aromaAlN","text_ar":"اَرْمَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (T, S, M.) ―         -b2-  [Hence, perhaps,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aromaAlN mino A_ibilK","text_ar":"اَرْمَالٌ مِنْ اـِبِلٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A number of camels in a state of dispersion."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"page_break","n":1160},{"kind":"text","text":"Also, the sing., [as a coll. gen. n.,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Lines,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"streaks, upon the legs of the wild cow,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon her fore legs and kind legs,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"differing from the rest of her colour:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, K:) n. un. ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ramalapN","text_ar":"رَمَلَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA. [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rumolapN","text_ar":"رُمْلَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) ―         -b4-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A redundance,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an excess,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ziyaAdapN","text_ar":"زِيَادَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",) in a thing. (K.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~amalu","text_ar":"الرَّمَلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also the name of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain kind of metre of verse;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, M, K;) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the eighth kind;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the measure of which is"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"originally"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"composed of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faAEilaAtuno","text_ar":"فَاعِلَاتُنْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"six times;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;) so called from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~amalu","text_ar":"الرَّمَلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifying “ a certain kind of walk or pace, ” inf. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ramala","text_ar":"رَمَلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]: (M, K: *) and Kh says that it is also applied to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any meagre verse"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"poetry, incongruous in structure;"},{"kind":"text","text":"such being so named by the Arabs without their defining anything respecting it; as, for instance, the saying [of 'Abeed Ibn-El-Abras (TA in arts."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*nb","text_ar":"ذنب"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qTb","text_ar":"قطب"},{"kind":"text","text":")],"},{"kind":"quote","text":"faAlquTabiy~aAtu faAl*~anuwbu \n                      \n                     \n                        A^aqofara mino A^aholihi maloHwbu"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Melhoob"},{"kind":"text","text":"(the name of a place, K in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lHb","text_ar":"لحب"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"has become destitute of its inhabitants, and El- Kutabeeyát,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(by which is meant a certain water, called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlquTabiy~apu","text_ar":"القُطَبِيَّةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with its environs, K* and TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qTb","text_ar":"قطب"},{"kind":"text","text":",)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and Edh-Dhanoob"},{"kind":"text","text":"(the name of a place, TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*nb","text_ar":"ذنب"},{"kind":"text","text":")]: he says also that, generally,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"majozuwo'","text_ar":"مَجْزُوْء"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what is curtailed of two of the original feet,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what consists of two feet only,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is thus called by them: accord. to IJ, it is applied by them to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"verse,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"poetry, that is incongruous, unsound,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"faulty, in structure,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such as falls short of the original"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"standard so as not to answer completely to any regular kind or species"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (M, TA:) thus it signifies as first explained above, and also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any verse,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"poetry, that is not such as is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaSiyd","text_ar":"قَصِيد"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as meaning that of which the hemistichs are complete"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nor such as is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajaz","text_ar":"رَجَز"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which some hold to be not verse, or poetry, but a kind of rhyming prose]. (IJ, M, K. *) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zamalN","text_ar":"زَمَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]"}],"source_refs":["IAar","T","TA","S","M","K"]}]}}